br&ht=edition| oclc =39793535 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ohiocivilwar.com/cw61.html Ohio in the Civil War: 61st Ohio Volunteer Infantry by Larry Stevens]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101229062412/http://ohsweb.ohiohistory.org/exhibits/fftc/relicroom/details.aspx?war=2&flagid=401&unitid=148&warname=Civil%20War National flag of the 61st Ohio Infantry]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101229062351/http://ohsweb.ohiohistory.org/exhibits/fftc/relicroom/details.aspx?war=2&flagid=400&unitid=148&warname=Civil%20War National flag of the 61st Ohio Infantry]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101229062418/http://ohsweb.ohiohistory.org/exhibits/fftc/relicroom/details.aspx?war=2&flagid=402&unitid=148&warname=Civil%20War National flag of the 61st Ohio Infantry]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101229062422/http://ohsweb.ohiohistory.org/exhibits/fftc/relicroom/details.aspx?war=2&flagid=403&unitid=148&warname=Civil%20War Regimental flag of the 61st Ohio Infantry]\n\n{{portal|American Civil War|Ohio}}\n{{Ohio in the Civil War}}\n{{American Civil War |expanded=CTCBS}}\n\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in 1862]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations disestablished in 1865]]\n[[Category:Ohio Civil War regiments]]\n[[Category:1862 establishments in Ohio]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Military Unit\n|unit_name= 61st Regiment, Ohio Volunteer Infantry\n|image=\n|dates= April 23, 1862, to March 31, 1865\n|country= [[United States]]\n|allegiance= [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]]\n|branch= [[Infantry]]\n|equipment= \n<!-- Culture and history -->\n|battles=[[Second_Battle_of_Bull_Run#August_28:_Brawner.27s_Farm_.28Groveton.29|Battle of Groveton]]<br/>[[Second Battle of Bull Run]]<br/>[[Battle of Chancellorsville]]<br/>[[Gettysburg Campaign]]<br/>[[Battle of Gettysburg]]<br/>[[Battle of Wauhatchie]]<br/>[[Atlanta Campaign]]<br/>[[Battle of Resaca]]<br/>[[Battle of Dallas]]<br/>[[Battle of New Hope Church]]<br/>[[Battle of Allatoona]]<br